#### 1. Triple Regex.Replace chain + `.ToLower()` in Underscore (4 allocations/call)
**Impact:** 4 intermediate string allocations per call × millions of calls = massive GC pressure.
**Files:** `CaseTransformExtensions.cs:L115-121`
**Fix:** Replace with a single-pass `StringBuilder` or `string.Create` approach that walks the input once, inserting underscores at boundaries and lowercasing in-place:
```csharp
public static string Underscore(this string input)
{
    if (string.IsNullOrEmpty(input)) return input;

    var sb = new StringBuilder(input.Length + 4);
    for (int i = 0; i < input.Length; i++)
    {
        char c = input[i];
        if (c == '-' || c == ' ')
        {
            sb.Append('_');
        }
        else if (char.IsUpper(c))
        {
            if (i > 0 && (char.IsLower(input[i - 1]) || char.IsDigit(input[i - 1])))
                sb.Append('_');
            else if (i > 0 && i + 1 < input.Length && char.IsUpper(input[i - 1]) && char.IsLower(input[i + 1]))
                sb.Append('_');
            sb.Append(char.ToLowerInvariant(c));
        }
        else
        {
            sb.Append(c);
